main event: The USS Lansing reported sighting one unidentified flying object (UFO) on June 17, 1963.
interesting points: The UFO was similar in appearance to a first-magnitude star or planet.
The UFO was initially sighted at an elevation of 83 degrees and faded at a bearing of 030 degrees.
The location of the sighting was 25.30N, 162.20W.
The sighting lasted from 17/0612Z to 17/0622Z (approximately 10 minutes).
The sky was clear, and no unusual weather conditions were noted.
sighted object: one object similar in appearance to a first-magnitude star or planet
